title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1986-12-15
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) > KORG AudioGate 4 > FLAC 24/96; Edited & Mastered in Audacity by Joe Noel: Flac 24/96; Checksum & tags created in xACT; 24 bit to 16 bit with MusicConverter using sox-14-4-2
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Grey
CC Rider
When Push Comes To Shove
Beat It On Down The Line >
Greatest Story Ever Told
Loser
Cassidy
Althea
My Brother Esau
Candyman
Let It Grow

Set 2

Iko Iko
Looks Like Rain
Black Muddy River
Playing In The Band >
Terrapin Station >
Drums >
Space >
Truckin' >
Wharf Rat >
Playing In The Band >
Good Lovin'

Encore:
Johnny B. Goode

Jerry Garcia - Guitar
Bob Weir - Guitar
Brent Mydland - Keyboards
Phil Lesh - Bass
Bill Kreutzmann - Drums
Mickey Hart - Drums

reviews.review_text: touch of grey  jerry come back dont think there was a dry eye  in the house  the night was magic  but it was the begining  of the  end of small venues to stadiums  the band played as good as ever   but lost was the show up about get  about  were u wana to be  to feel the music  the phil zone  away from the crzy screaming  jerry   i had start dodging  drunks on acid bad sound  know  thats why i love the archives  afther all this  time  these recording sound  better than being there     so i had write this down   enjoy
